(82, '1', '3', 'C', 'FK018', 'RS0101', '<p><strong>SOAL UTS BHS INGGRI</strong><strong>S 1</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PART 1</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>LISTENING SECTION (SCORE 30</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>QUESTIONS</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1.&nbsp; Jenny is looking for ______.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A.&nbsp;&nbsp; Rob</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; B.&nbsp;&nbsp; Luke</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; C.&nbsp;&nbsp; Henry</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Jenny _______ able to rent a car.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A. was</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; B. wasn&#39;t</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Jenny ______ Henry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A. meets</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; B. talks to</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; C. leaves a message with</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4.&nbsp; Jenny wants to apologize for ______.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A. not responding to Luke&#39;s texts</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; B. taking so long to call Luke</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; C. leaving suddenly</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; D. being rude</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Luke wants to apologize for ______.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A. taking so long to fix Jenny&#39;s computer</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; B. not responding to Jenny&#39;s texts</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; C. leaving suddenly</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; D. being rude</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Jenny&#39;s ______ is broken.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A. laptop</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; B. suitcase</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; C. suitcase lock</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; D. rental car</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. Luke thinks that Henry _______</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;A. has gone on a walk</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; B. went for a drive</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; C.went shopping</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; D.is in danger</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. Luke thinks that Henry _______ be on time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A.will definitely</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; B.will probably</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; C.will probably not</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; D.will definitely not</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9. Jenny takes a nap because she ______.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A.drank too much last night</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; B.took some medication</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; C.has jet lag</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10. When Jenny wakes up, Henry _____ home.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A.&nbsp;&nbsp; is</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; B.&nbsp;&nbsp; isn&#39;t</p>\r\n\r\n<p>11. Andrew Page was attacked ________.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A.&nbsp;&nbsp; at Heathrow Airport</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; B.&nbsp;&nbsp; on the street</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; C.&nbsp;&nbsp; in New York</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; D.&nbsp; in his home</p>\r\n\r\n<p>12. Mr. Page is ______.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A.&nbsp;&nbsp; dead</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; B.&nbsp;&nbsp; in jail</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; C.&nbsp;&nbsp; in the hospital</p>\r\n\r\n<p>13. Mr. Page does research on ______.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A.&nbsp;&nbsp; drugs and medicine</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; B.&nbsp;&nbsp; renewable energy</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; C.&nbsp;&nbsp; computer chips</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; D.&nbsp; weapons</p>\r\n\r\n<p>14. Jenny _______ Andrew Page.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A.&nbsp;&nbsp; knows</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; B.&nbsp;&nbsp; doesn&#39;t know</p>\r\n\r\n<p>15. After she sees the news, Jenny calls ______</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;A. Rob</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; B. Luke</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; C.Henry</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PART 2</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>GRAMMAR (SCORE 20)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1.&nbsp;<em>Change these sentences into &ldquo;<strong>simple present, past tense</strong> or <strong>simple future</strong>&rdquo; as well as change the adverb of that tense related to the tenses below</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp;Contoh :</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;Simple Present</strong> : I drink milk every day</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;Past Tense</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; : I drank milk yesterday</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;Simple Future</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; : I will drink milk tomorrow/I am going to drink milk tomorrow</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:top; width:213px\">\r\n			<p><strong>SIMPLE PRESENT</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:top; width:213px\">\r\n			<p><strong>PAST TENSE</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:top; width:213px\">\r\n			<p><strong>SIMPLE FUTURE</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top; width:213px\">\r\n			<p>I get up at five o&rsquo;clock every day</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top; width:213px\">\r\n			<p><strong>&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..</strong></p>\r\n