(831, '1', '3', 'C', 'IS402', 'HJ9101', '<p>1. A symbol to describes a sequence of actions that provide something of measurable value to an actor and is drawn as a horizontal ellipse, that is :</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>use case</li>\r\n	<li>actor</li>\r\n	<li>association</li>\r\n	<li>boundary</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Requirement gathering is always the first step in any software analysis activity. Based on the requirements, the software engineer (analyst) can create a set of scenarios that each identify a thread of usage for the system to be constructed. The scenarios is provide a description of how the system will be used. The scenarios often is called as :</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>activity</li>\r\n	<li>use cases</li>\r\n	<li>analysis</li>\r\n	<li>identification gathering</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>3. A person, organization, or external system that plays a role in one or more interactions with your system and drawn them as stick figures.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>use case</li>\r\n	<li>actor</li>\r\n	<li>association</li>\r\n	<li>boundary</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>4. A solid line between actors and use cases are indicated in use case diagrams is known as :</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>use case</li>\r\n	<li>actor</li>\r\n	<li>association</li>\r\n	<li>boundary</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>5. An association exists whenever an actor is involved with an interaction described by a :</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>use case</li>\r\n	<li>actor</li>\r\n	<li>association</li>\r\n	<li>boundary</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>6. A rectangle around the use cases, called the system &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. box, to indicates the scope of your system.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>use case</li>\r\n	<li>actor</li>\r\n	<li>association</li>\r\n	<li>boundary</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>7. Teknologi objek mengimplementasikan penerapan :</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Pengembangan iteratif</li>\r\n	<li>Menggunakan arsitektur berbasis terstruktur</li>\r\n	<li>Spesifikasi konfigurasi sistem yang besar</li>\r\n	<li>Pemrograman 4GL</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>8. CRC :</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>class-relationship-card</li>\r\n	<li>card-relationship-class</li>\r\n	<li>class-responsibilities-card</li>\r\n	<li>collaborator-responsibility-card</li>\r\n	<li>class-responsibility-collaborator</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>9. Use-case yang diekstraksi dari use-case yang lebih kompleks.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>abstract use-case</li>\r\n	<li>extend use-case</li>\r\n	<li>execution use-case</li>\r\n	<li>event use-case</li>\r\n	<li>uses use-case</li>\r\n	<li>include use-case</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>10. Use-cases extracted from more complex use-cases.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>abstract use-case</li>\r\n	<li>extend use-case</li>\r\n	<li>execution use-case</li>\r\n	<li>event use-case</li>\r\n	<li>uses use-case</li>\r\n	<li>include use-case</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>11. Include use case is used when ...</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>More than one use case is associated with a use case</li>\r\n	<li>There is one usecase initiated by another use</li>\r\n	<li>One use case initiates one or more other use cases</li>\r\n	<li>One use case is initiated by one or more other use cases</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>12.&nbsp; &nbsp;An actor who represents the behavior of another actor.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Main business actors</li>\r\n	<li>Main system actors</li>\r\n	<li>Abstract actor</li>\r\n	<li>Recipient actor</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;13.. Integrated software development tools that provide all the necessary facilities to develop new application software with maximum speed and quality.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>a. ADEs/IDEs</li>\r\n	<li>b. CASE</li>\r\n	<li>c. Ration Rose</li>\r\n	<li>d. architect</li>\r\n	<li>e. Repositories</li>\r\n	<li>f. Middleware</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>13. System development strategy that emphasizes drawing system models to assist visualization and analysis &amp; design of information systems.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>a. Data Modelling</li>\r\n	<li>b. Prototype</li>\r\n	<li>c. rad</li>\r\n	<li>d. Model-driven development</li>\r\n	<li>e. Product-driven process</li>\r\n	<li>f. Object Oriented Models</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;14. Stakeholders who serve the needs of use-case users.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>actor</li>\r\n	<li>temporal actor</li>\r\n	<li>external actors</li>\r\n	<li>primary system actor</li>\r\n	<li>primary business actor</li>\r\n	<li>external server actors</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>kasus:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Serangkaian peristiwa berikut menggambarkan proses bisnis dari kegiatan pemeriksaan kesehatan (berobat) di sebuah klinik kesehatan;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>pasien datang ke loket pendaftaran &nbsp;&nbsp;untuk melakukan pendaftaran dengan membawa kartu berobat, petugas loket memeriksa data pasien untuk ditetapkan sebagai peserta pemeriksaan kesehatan hari ini;</li>\r\n	<li>pasien memasuki ruang periksa untuk dilakukan pemeriksaan oleh petugas medis/dokter;</li>\r\n	<li>pasien mendapatkan tindakan medis yang dilakukan oleh petugas medis/dokter; kemungkinan pasien mendapat tindakan medis berupa tes lab bisa saja terjadi yang dilakukan oleh tenaga laboratorium(laboran);</li>\r\n	<li>pasien menerima resep untuk pengambilan obat di apotik yang diserahkan oleh petugas apotik/apoteker.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Dari alur proses bisnis di atas tentu dapat direpresentasikan ke dalam diagram proses bisnis yang tepat. Saudara diminta mengekspresikannya sesuai dengan kaedah pembuatan diagram proses bisnis yang saudara ketahui. Kemudian tuangkan ke dalam komposisi usecase dari sistem yang terbentuk. &nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '2022/2023', '3', '1', '2022-12-24 11:34:50', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
