;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; : Anyway, this book represents Luis&rsquo;s life now. He wants to &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; (2) his</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; grades,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; so he is going to &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;(3)harder this year. This picture of a book represents</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; that</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Steven&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; : Uh-uhh</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ana&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; : This airplane represents the future. Luis said he&rsquo;d like to &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. (4) around the&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; world someday. He also wants to &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..&nbsp;&nbsp; (5) a job in a foreign country</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>LISTENING 2</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>QUESTIONS</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Why can&#39;t the first man give Jenny directions?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; A. He is lost.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; B.He is busy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; C. He doesn&#39;t live there.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. What does the second man tell Jenny?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; A. The Tate Modern is closed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; B. The Tate Modern is nearby.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; C. The Tate Modern is far away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Why does Rob apologize?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A. He is late.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;B. The weather is bad.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;C.The Tate Modern is closed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Where else does Rob suggest visiting?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;A. The Globe Theatre</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;B. The Thames River</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;C. A Power Station</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. How does Jenny feel about Shakespeare?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; A. She likes him.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; B. She doesn&#39;t like him.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PART 2</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>VOCABULARY </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>A. Check and match the following statements to the correct order&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>I enjoy helping others&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A. friendly and outgoing</li>\r\n	<li>I always try to tell the truth&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; B. optimistic and positive</li>\r\n	<li>I like talking with people&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; C. hardworking and ambitious</li>\r\n	<li>Nothing gives me stress&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; D. laid-back and relaxed</li>\r\n	<li>I make people laugh&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; E. kind and generous</li>\r\n	<li>I work hard to achieve my goals&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; F. strong and independent</li>\r\n	<li>I try to look on the bright side of life&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; G. humorous and entertaining</li>\r\n	<li>No one can tell me how to live my life&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; H. honest and sincere</li>\r\n	<li>I want to eat because of&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; I. thirsty</li>\r\n	<li>I want to drink because of&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; J. hungrY</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>B. <strong>Complete the text from the words in the Box</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>installed&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; writing papers&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; communication&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; few people&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; a man</p>\r\n\r\n<p>By the early 1990&#39;s, people were using computers in many different ways. Computers were already &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. (1)&nbsp; in most schools, offices, and homes. They were commonly used for &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..(2) , playing games, financial accounting, and business productivity applications. But very &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..(3)&nbsp; used them for &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..(4), research, and shopping the way we do now. &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;(5)&nbsp; named Tim Berners-Lee changed all that.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PART 3</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>GRAMMAR</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Change these sentences from Active into passive</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. John sends two emails everyday</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Passive : ........</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. My brother washes his car everyday</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Passive : ........</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. I saved my money in bank last week</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Passive : .....</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4.&nbsp; I do my job in my office everyday</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Passive : ......</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. They are attending newly meeting now</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Passive : ......</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '2022/2023', '3', '1', '2023-04-12 08:46:23', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
