(2687, '5', '1', 'C', 'SMPK104', 'EF2301', '<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>TRANSLATION</strong><strong> &ndash; 20 points</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Read the text carefully!</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Doctor Bugs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most people don&rsquo;t like bugs, but Doctor Mark Moffett &nbsp;&nbsp;loves them! In fact, his nickname is Doctor Bugs. He&rsquo;s a photographer and an entomologist. An entomologist studies bugs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Doctor Moffett&rsquo;s favorite bug is the ant. He goes all over the world to study ants. He watches them as they eat, work, rest, sleep, and fight.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He takes photographs of the ants. He lies on the ground with his camera and waits for the right moment. The ants and other bugs often bite him, but that doesn&rsquo;t stop Doctor Bugs. He has an interesting and unusual job, and he loves it!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Translate the story into Bahasa Indonesia with your own sentences (minimum 100 words)!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>COMPLETE THE SENTENCES</strong><strong> &ndash; 10 points</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Complete each sentence with the correct form of the verb in parentheses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. A zookeeper &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..&nbsp; (feed) animals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Computer programmers &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..&nbsp; (write) software.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Photographers &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&nbsp; (take) photos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. A chef &nbsp;&nbsp;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. (cook) food.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. A firefighter&nbsp; &nbsp;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;. (fight) fires.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Musicians &nbsp;&nbsp;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. (play) instruments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. A farmer &nbsp;&nbsp;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; &nbsp;(work) on a farm.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. A dancer &nbsp;&nbsp;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;. (dance).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9. The manager &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;. (work) at the office</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10. The salesman &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;. (get) his first costumer</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>WRITE THE SENTENCES</strong><strong> &ndash; 30 points</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Write each verb with the correct -s, -es, or -ies ending then make the sentences!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Study &nbsp;&nbsp;: &nbsp;studies &agrave; He studies hard</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Help</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Fish</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Miss</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Pass</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Fly</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. Worry</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. Fix</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9. Explore&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10. Watch</p>\r\n\r\n<p>11. Bite</p>\r\n\r\n<p>13. Like</p>\r\n\r\n<p>14. Buy</p>\r\n\r\n<p>15. Pay</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>ADJECTIVE SENTENCES</strong><strong> &ndash; 20 points</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once upon a time, there was a big tree in a forest. Under this tree lived a bunch of tiny ants. These ants were very hardworking and they had a special talent. They could build bridges.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One sunny day, a big rainstorm hit the forest, the raindrops fell heavily and the little ants got stuck on one side of big puddle. They needed to get to the other side where there was food and safety but the water was too wide for them to cross alone.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The ants knew they had to work together, they formed a line, one aunt connecting to the next and slowly they began to build a bridge. They used sticks leaves and their tiny bodies to create a path over the water. It was hard work and the rain kept pouring but they didn&rsquo;t give up one by one.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The ants crossed the bridge they had built together. It was incredible to see how they helped each other, even when the rain made things tough. The last ant to cross was the smallest of them all. It was scared because it had never done anything like this before but with the support of its fellow ants it made it across safely.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As the last ant reached the other side, the rain stopped. The tiny ants looked back at the bridge they had built and felt a great sense of accomplishment. They had shown that when they worked together. They could overcome any obstacle no matter how big or small.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And so the ants lived happily under their big tree. Knowing that teamwork and unity could help them, face any challenge that came their way they had learned that together. They were strong just like the bridge they had built.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Make 10 adjectives sentences from this story.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><strong>PRESENT CONTINUOUS </strong><strong>&ndash; 20 &nbsp;points</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Change this verb into simple present continuous and make the sentences</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Wake up</li>\r\n	<li>Clean</li>\r\n	<li>Work</li>\r\n	<li>Laugh</li>\r\n	<li>Smile</li>\r\n	<li>Show</li>\r\n	<li>Dream</li>\r\n	<li>Rain</li>\r\n	<li>Climb</li>\r\n	<li>Interest</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '', '2023/2024', '3', '1', '2023-11-04 03:37:20', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(2688, '6', '1', 'A', 'SMPKAK104', 'HK0208', '<p><strong>I. Read about Mike Miller and Kelly Smith. &nbsp;Then, answer the questions below.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Mike Miller</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m an English teacher and I have a big family, so I have a very busy daily routine! First, I get up every day at six o&rsquo;clock, get&nbsp;washed and dressed, and leave for work byseven- thirty. I get to school at eight o&rsquo;clock. I prepare my lessons and then teach until noon. The others teachers and I always eat lunch and talk together in the teachers&rsquo; room. I teach again in the afternoon and then I correct my students&rsquo; homework and tests.&nbsp; After I get back home, I help my kids with their homework. I have three kids in elementary school. Their names are Mathew, Jon and Suzie. Then, I do some exercise, eat dinner with my family and watch TV before I go to bed at about ten o&rsquo;clock. We love to watch travel shows. Finally, I read in bed for a few minutes before I fall asleep.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Kelly Smith</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Well, I almost always get up very early, at about five-thirty. I get up early because I like to go jogging along the beach and watch the sun rise. Later, after breakfast, I go to&nbsp; work. I work in a bank near my home.&nbsp;I don&rsquo;t drive to work, I take a bus. It only takes about twenty minutes to get to work.&nbsp; After work, I like to go to my favorite bakery and buy some fresh bread. I get home between five o&rsquo;clock and five-thirty. My husband Michael usually makes dinner because he loves to cook. In fact, he is a chef in a restaurant. His hobby is painting, and my hobby is growing flowers in our garden. We also have a pet dog called Wolfie. In the evenings we take Wolfie for a walk, and then get to bed by nine-thirty because we have to get up so early again the next morning.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>What does Mike do?</li>\r\n	<li>What does Kelly do?</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '', '2023/2024', '3', '1', '2023-11-04 03:38:13', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(2690, '6', '1', 'A', 'SMPKAK104', 'HK0208', '<ol>\r\n	<li>What time does Mike get up?</li>\r\n	<li>What time does Kelly get up?</li>\r\n	<li>Where does Mike have lunch?</li>\r\n	<li>How does Kelly get to work</li>\r\n	<li>When does Mike watch TV?&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>What is Kelly&rsquo;s hobby?&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Where does Mike read</li>\r\n	<li>What time does Kelly go to bed? &nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>II. <strong>Choose the correct word to complete each sentence.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>The empty house was completely &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. (silent / silently).</li>\r\n	<li>There was a &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; (fresh / freshly) fall of snow during the night.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;All information will be treated as strictly &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; (confidential / confidentially).</li>\r\n	<li>I think it is unlikely that we will move in the &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;. (near / nearly) future.</li>\r\n	<li>The lights are too &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; (bright<strong> </strong>/ brightly) in here &ndash; they are hurting my eyes.</li>\r\n	<li>42. He was getting &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; (bored / boring / boringly) of doing the same thing every day.</li>\r\n	<li>I would like you to give me an &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; (honest / honestly) answer.</li>\r\n	<li>An &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. (immediate / immediately) effect of the war has been a breakdown of law and order.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Ann makes &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;. (beautiful / beautifully) cakes.</li>\r\n	<li>The article described &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; (recent / recently) developments in the search for a cure for AIDS.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>III. Compose one of your favourite place that you&rsquo;ve visited on your holiday!.</strong></p>\r\n', '', '2023/2024', '3', '1', '2023-11-04 03:39:13', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
