(2753, '6', '1', 'B', 'SMPKAK104', 'HK0208', '<p><strong>. Read about Mike Miller and Kelly Smith. &nbsp;Then, answer the questions below.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Mike Miller</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>I&rsquo;m an English teacher and I have a big family, so I have a very busy daily routine! First, I get up every day at six o&rsquo;clock, get&nbsp;washed and dressed, and leave for work byseven- thirty. I get to school at eight o&rsquo;clock. I prepare my lessons and then teach until noon. The others teachers and I always eat lunch and talk together in the teachers&rsquo; room. I teach again in the afternoon and then I correct my students&rsquo; homework and tests.&nbsp; After I get back home, I help my kids with their homework. I have three kids in elementary school. Their names are Mathew, Jon and Suzie. Then, I do some exercise, eat dinner with my family and watch TV before I go to bed at about ten o&rsquo;clock. We love to watch travel shows. Finally, I read in bed for a few minutes before I fall asleep.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Kelly Smith</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Well, I almost always get up very early, at about five-thirty. I get up early because I like to go jogging along the beach and watch the sun rise. Later, after breakfast, I go to&nbsp; work. I work in a bank near my home.&nbsp;I don&rsquo;t drive to work, I take a bus. It only takes about twenty minutes to get to work.&nbsp; After work, I like to go to my favorite bakery and buy some fresh bread. I get home between five o&rsquo;clock and five-thirty. My husband Michael usually makes dinner because he loves to cook. In fact, he is a chef in a restaurant. His hobby is painting, and my hobby is growing flowers in our garden. We also have a pet dog called Wolfie. In the evenings we take Wolfie for a walk, and then get to bed by nine-thirty because we have to get up so early again the next morning.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>What does Mike do?</li>\r\n	<li>What does Kelly do?</li>\r\n	<li>What time does Mike get up?</li>\r\n	<li>What time does Kelly get up?</li>\r\n	<li>Where does Mike have lunch?</li>\r\n	<li>How does Kelly get to work</li>\r\n	<li>When does Mike watch TV?&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>What is Kelly&rsquo;s hobby?&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Where does Mike read</li>\r\n	<li>What time does Kelly go to bed? &nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>II. <strong>Choose the correct word to complete each sentence.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>The empty house was completely &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. (silent / silently).</li>\r\n	<li>There was a &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; (fresh / freshly) fall of snow during the night.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;All information will be treated as strictly &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; (confidential / confidentially).</li>\r\n	<li>I think it is unlikely that we will move in the &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;. (near / nearly) future.</li>\r\n	<li>The lights are too &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; (bright<strong> </strong>/ brightly) in here &ndash; they are hurting my eyes.</li>\r\n	<li>42. He was getting &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; (bored / boring / boringly) of doing the same thing every day.</li>\r\n	<li>I would like you to give me an &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; (honest / honestly) answer.</li>\r\n	<li>An &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. (immediate / immediately) effect of the war has been a breakdown of law and order.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Ann makes &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;. (beautiful / beautifully) cakes.</li>\r\n	<li>The article described &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; (recent / recently) developments in the search for a cure for AIDS.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>III. Compose one of your favourite place that you&rsquo;ve visited on your holiday!.</strong></p>\r\n', '', '2023/2024', '3', '1', '2023-11-04 04:14:23', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
