(4252, '5', '1', 'C', 'SMPK104', 'EF2301', '<p><strong>MATA KULIAH :&nbsp; GENERAL ENGLISH</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SEMESTER : 1 TAHUN 2023 / 2024</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Dosen : Euis Fauziah, S.Pd, M.Pd</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>A. Read the text carefully</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why I am studying botanic</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hi, I&#39;m Dave and I&#39;d like to talk about the time when I decided to become a physicist. It seemed to be a strong possibility but as I hadn&#39;t prepared for my required exams, there was a slim chance of passing them. In the end, I decided to try my luck at botany instead. This as it turned out was a fantastic decision</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I adored every second of my studies made some lifelong friends and discovered more about myself in the process. I&#39;m currently working through my degree and by the end of next year, I will be fully qualified and ready to make my way in the world. Just think all of this came from me &quot;failing&quot; my original exams. Talk about a successful mistake</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>I. Fill in the blanks</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. I decided to try my luck at _______________ instead</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. law</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. chemistry</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. botany</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. engineering</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. I ____________ every second of my studies</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. loved</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. hated</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. adored</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. abhorred</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Talk about a ___________ mistake</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. successful</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. bad</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. great</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. poor</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>II. Answer the question</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. What does Dave want to do?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>_________________________</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. What does &quot;a slim chance&quot; mean?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>____________________________</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. What did Dave study in the end?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>______________________________</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. What will happen at the end of next year?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>_____________________________________</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. What does Dave mean by a &quot;successful&rdquo; mistake?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>_______________________________________</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>III. Talk about yourself</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Are you happy with what you studied/studying?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>___________________________________________</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Is it important to go to university to have a successful career?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>_____________________________________________</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Do you know anybody successful who didn&#39;t go to university?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>B. Read the text carefully and translate into Bahasa Indonesia</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Open for business</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dion really wanted to open his own business. He loved watching shows on TV about people who invented great things and helped other people who love their inventions too. He tried to learn about how people started their own businesses and how they got their great ideas, but a lot of it, was too hard for him to understand yet. His mom suggested that he look around the community for a business leader which might be able to help him understand, so that he could start his own business one day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One day, he and his mom were out getting ice cream and the shop owner, Mr. Warner was the one serving them. Dion&#39;s mom asked if he had a few minutes to talk and Mr. Warner sat down with them</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Mr. Warner, Dion really wants to open his own business one day. Do you think you could help him understand how to run a business?&quot; Dion&#39;s mom asked.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;I can try,&quot; replied Mr. Warner, &quot;but a lot of, it is hard to understand. There is a lot of math and plenty of things you just have to learn through trial and error.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;A lot of math?&quot; asked Dion, &quot;Why do you need to know math to run a business?&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>I. Make this verbs into present progressive tense</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1.&nbsp; Talk</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Decided</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Prepare</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Try</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Turn</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Study</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. Discover</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. Work</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9. Fail</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10. Open</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>II. Change this word into affirmative, negative, interrogative sentences</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Watch</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Show</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Help</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Get</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Understand</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Look</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. Start</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. Talk</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9. Sit</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10. Think</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '2023/2024', '4', '1', '2024-01-08 10:35:43', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
