(4464, '5', '1', 'C', 'SMPK104', 'HY2024', '<p>UJIAN AKHIR SEMESTER TAHUN AKADEMIK 2023/2024</p>\r\n\r\n<p>MATA KULIAH : GENERAL ENGLISH A2</p>\r\n\r\n<p>DOSEN : dra. Hirayanti, MM. MSi</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HARI/TANGGAL : Sabtu, 13 Januari 2024</p>\r\n\r\n<p>WAKTU : 09.00&ndash; 10.30</p>\r\n\r\n<p>TIPE SOAL : Closed book - offline</p>\r\n\r\n<p>STUDENT&rsquo;S NAME :</p>\r\n\r\n<p>NPM :</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Buyers, sellers and the market</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A. Customers and clients</p>\r\n\r\n<p>People who buy IBM&rsquo;s products and services are IBM&rsquo;s customers or clients.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Foster and Partners, a big architectural firm, has clients, rather than customers. Client often refers to people and organizations who buy the services of professionals such as accountants, lawyers, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>IBM&rsquo;s customers considered as a group make up its customer base. Foster and Partners&rsquo; clients considered as a group form a client base. These are slightly technical expressions, used for example in business journalism.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>People who buy a company&rsquo;s or a professional&rsquo;s products or services, especially expensive or exclusive ones, are its clientele. (note : Clientele is rarely used in the plural)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can also talk about the users of a product or service who may not be the organizations who actually buy it. The expression end-users refers especially to people who use products, particularly computer equipment and other technology. These expressions are often used in contrast to the producers and distributors of a product. For example, IBM sells products through various channels, but the end-users are the employees of the companies that buy its products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>People who buy products or services for their own use are consumers, especially when considered as members of large groups of people buying things in advanced economies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>B. Buyers, sellers and vendors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A person or organization that buys something is a buyer or purchaser. But these terms are also used to talk about someone in a company or shop responsible for buying goods that it uses or sells. These people are also buying managers or purchasing managers. An industrial buyer is an organization that buys things for use in producing its own goods or services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A person or organization that sells something is a seller. In some contex6s, for example selling property, they are referred to as the vendor. (Business journalist and lawyers may also refer to people selling products, rather than services, as vendors.).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>People selling things in the street are street vendors. A vending machine is a machine from which you can buy coffee, cigarettes, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>C. The market</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The market, the free market and market economy are used to talk about an economic system where prices, jobs, wages, etc. depend on what people want to buy, how much they are willing to pay, etc. rather than being controlled by a government. In this sense, market is often used in these combination</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Market forces / market pressures = used to talk about the way that a market economy makes sellers produce what people want to buy, at prices they are willing to pay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Market-place = producers and buyers in a particular market economy, the way they behave, etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Market prices = prices that people are willing to pay, rather than ones fixed by a government.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; Market reforms = changes to an economy made by a government so that it becomes more like a market economy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Note: Market pressures occurs more frequently in the context of financial markets such as stock markets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>EXERCISES</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I. Match each beginning (1-6) with its continuation to make true statements containing expressions from A article. (20)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. The Richard Rogers partnership has some prestigious clients -....</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Louis Vuitton luggage appeals to .......</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Telefonica&rsquo;s client base grew 15 per cent, ......</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Microsoft sells Vista to end-users ......</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. BSkyB said 92,000 new customers had signed up for its products in the last quarters, ........</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Centrica, owner of British Gas, angered customers by announcing pre-tax profits of almost &pound;1 billion ..........</p>\r\n\r\n<p>a. One day after increasing its customers&rsquo; gas bill by a record 35 per cent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>b. Spanish Airport Authority , for example.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>c. An upmarket clientele</p>\r\n\r\n<p>d. Bringing its customer base to 8.98 million.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>e. And also to major manufactures, such as Dell and HP</p>\r\n\r\n<p>f. To 245.1m, from the end of June last year to the same time this year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>II. Find appropriate forms of expressions in A and B article that refer to the following. (20)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1. Someone who buys food in a supermarket (4 expressions)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. All the people who buy food from a particular supermarket chain, from the point of view of the chain.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Someone who buys the services of a private detective agency.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. All the people who buy the services of the agency, seen as a group (2 expressions)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Someone who sells goods or services</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Someone selling a house (2 expressions)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7. Someone buying a house (2 expressions)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>8. Someone who sells hamburgers to tourists outside the Tower of London.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>9. Someone whose job is buying tyres for a car company (4 expressions)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>10. Someone who uses a computer, even if they have not bought it themselves, but their company has (2 expressions)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>III. Complete the TV reporter&rsquo;s commentary with expression from C article containing &lsquo;market&rsquo;. (market forces, market pressures, market place, market price, market reforms, market economy) (20)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lsquo;in China, all economic activity used to be controlled by the state. Prices were fixed by the government, not by buyers and sellers in the (1)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; But in the last 20 years there has been a series of (2) &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.that have allowed people to go into business and start their own companies. (3)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;..are determined by what buyers are willing to pay, no longer by the state. There are still state-owned companies that lose a lot of money. Until recently, they have been protected from (4)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; (2 possibilities), but (5) &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;(2 possibilities) will eventually mean that they close down. Of course, the (6) &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.. has its losers &ndash; those without work, and victims of crime, which used to be very rare.&rsquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>IV. OVER TO YOU (40)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; What companies in your country have a large customer base?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&bull; What is the purchasing manager responsible or buying in a large office?&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;GOOD LUCK</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '2023/2024', '4', '1', '2024-01-11 12:09:49', '2024-01-11 12:27:53'),
